aturn was already $1000 below market average for the class of cars, then after they reduce the dealer profit, it would be $2000 below market average. it will: 1) attract even more people to buy saturns because it would save them money. 2) force the competitors to lower their prices to survive. now, not only will saturn owners benefit from a lower dealer profit, even the buyers for other cars will pay less. isn't that saving money? $0.02, doug.
